  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An auditorium has seats for <math alttext=\"1,800\"><mn>1,800</mn>\n</math> people. Tickets to attend a show at the auditorium currently cost <math alttext=\"dollar sign 4.00\"><mo>$</mo><mn>4.00</mn>\n</math>. For each <math alttext=\"dollar sign 1.00\"><mo>$</mo><mn>1.00</mn>\n</math> increase to the ticket price, <math alttext=\"100\"><mn>100</mn>\n</math> fewer tickets will be sold. This situation can be modeled by the equation <math alttext=\"y equals minus 100 x squared plus 1,400 x plus 7,200\"><mrow>\n\t<mi>y</mi>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mo>-</mo>\n\t\t\t<mn>100</mn>\n\t\t\t<msup>\n\t\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t\t\t<mn>2</mn>\n\t\t\t</msup>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t\t<mo>+</mo>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mn>1,400</mn>\n\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t\t<mo>+</mo>\n\t\t<mn>7,200</mn>\n\t</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</math>, where <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> represents the increase in ticket price, in dollars, and <math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math> represents the revenue, in dollars, from ticket sales. If this equation is graphed in the <em>xy</em>-plane, at what value of <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> is the maximum of the graph?</p>",
